When you're craving crispy chicken, nothing beats panko, aka Japanese style bread crumbs, for their satisfying crunch.üçó Better yet, this Chicken Katsu-inspired rice bowl can go from pan to plate in 15 minutes! ‚è±
Recipe belowüëá:

INGREDIENTS
3 oz. Edamame
¬Ω oz. Pickled Ginger
3 fl. oz. Tonkatsu Sauce
2 Tbsp. Panko Breadcrumbs
8¬Ω oz. Cooked Jasmine Rice
¬Ω tsp. Badia Fried Rice Seasoning
2 Scallions
4 oz. Slaw Mix
12 oz. Boneless Skinless Chicken Breasts
¬Ω tsp. Sesame Seeds

DIRECTIONS
1. Preheat your oven to 400¬∞F. Place panko in an even layer on a plate. Pat chicken dry, then place chicken on panko, coating one side completely and pressing gently to adhere.

2. Place a medium oven-safe pan over medium heat and add 2 tsp. olive oil. Add chicken, panko side down, to hot pan and cook until browned, 3-4 minutes on one side.

3. Flip chicken, and place pan in hot oven. Roast until it reaches 165¬∞F, 8-10 minutes. While chicken roasts, prepare ingredients and cook rice.

4. Mince pickled ginger. Trim and thinly slice scallions, keeping whites and greens separate.

5. Place a large non-stick pan over medium high heat and add 2 tsp. olive oil. Add whites of green onions, edamame, a pinch of salt, and slaw mix to hot pan. Stir occasionally until slaw begins to brown, 2-3 minutes. Stir in seasoning blend until combined. Add rice, stirring to break up clumps until warmed through and vegetables are tender, 2-3 minutes.

6. Place tonkatsu sauce in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave until warmed through, for 30 seconds. Plate dish by slicing chicken and topping fried rice with ginger, chicken, tonkatsu sauce, scallion greens, and sesame seeds!

üçÖ Ingredients üßÄ 
¬Ω oz. Grated Parmesan
¬Ω tsp. Garlic Salt
4 fl. oz. Cream
¬º tsp. Red Pepper Flakes
16 oz. Italian Pork Sausage Links
2 Sprigs of Fresh Oregano
2 Tbsp. Tomato Paste
2 Garlic Cloves
10 oz. Penne Pasta
10 fl. oz. Tomato Sauce

üçù  Make the Pasta üçù 
1Ô∏è‚É£ Prep the ingredients: Stem oregano and coarsely chop. Mince garlic. Remove Italian sausage from its casing, if necessary.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Cook the sausage: Place a large pot over medium-high heat with 2 tsp. olive oil. Add sausage, breaking into smaller pieces until no pink remains and sausage reaches a minimum internal temperature of 160 degrees, 4-6 minutes.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Cook the pasta and sauce: Stir pasta, 2 Tbsp. tomato paste, garlic salt, 1 1/4 cups tomato sauce, garlic, oregano, and 2 1/4 cups water into hot pot. Cover, and bring to a boil. Stir often, scraping bottom of pot to prevent burning, until pasta is al dente, 10-12 minutes.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Finish pasta: Stir cream into hot pot and bring to a simmer. Once simmering, remove from burner and plate, topping with cheese and red pepper flakes to taste. Makes 4 generous servings.
